TALES have been told about domestic workers causing trouble and threatening marriages and relationships. Some stories include how they sneak around with men while their wives are away, while other horror stories tell how they are sexually assaulted by their bosses. SunReaders were asked on Facebook about their experiences with their helpers. “She went away and came back early to find the gogo and her madala boyfriend on the bed having fun.” Life coach and relationship expert Sonja Broschk said men are usually to blame. “Men take advantage merely because their partners are tired. “Men insist the helper sits down and has a drink. Out of fear of being fired, they do as they are told. Often they are foreigners without proper documentation,” she said.